GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
S 1
SENATE BILL 452
Short Title: End Child Marriage. (Public)
Sponsors: Senators Everitt, Grafstein, and Bradley (Primary Sponsors).
Referred to: Rules and Operations of the Senate
March 25, 2025
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO REQUIRE THAT ONLY INDIVIDUALS EIGHTEEN YEARS OR OLDER MAY
3 LAWFULLY MARRY.
4 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
5 SECTION 1. G.S. 51-2 reads as rewritten:
6 "§ 51-2. Lawful age to marry.
7 (a) All Only unmarried persons of 18 years, or older, may lawfully marry.
8 (a1) Persons over 16 years of age and under 18 years of age may marry a person no more
9 than four years older, and the register of deeds may issue a license for the marriage, only after
10 there has been filed with the register of deeds a certified copy of an order issued by a district
11 court authorizing the marriage as provided in G.S. 51-2.1, or a written consent to the marriage,
12 said consent having been signed by the appropriate person as follows:
13 (1) By a parent having full or joint legal custody of the underage party; or
14 (2) By a person, agency, or institution having legal custody or serving as a
15 guardian of the underage party.
16 Such written consent shall not be required for an emancipated minor if a certificate of
17 emancipation issued pursuant to Article 35 of Chapter 7B of the General Statutes or a certified
18 copy of a final decree or certificate of emancipation from this or any other jurisdiction is filed
19 with the register of deeds.
20 (b) Repealed by Session Laws 2021-119, s. 1, effective August 26, 2021, and applicable
21 to marriage licenses pending or issued on or after that date.
22 (b1) It shall be unlawful for any person under 16 years of age to marry.
23 (c) When a license to marry is procured by any person under 18 years of age by fraud or
24 misrepresentation, a parent of the underage party, a person, agency, or institution having legal
25 custody or serving as a guardian of the underage party, or a guardian ad litem appointed to
26 represent the underage party pursuant to G.S. 51-2.1(b) is a proper party to bring an action to
27 annul the marriage."
28 SECTION 2. G.S. 51-2.1 reads as rewritten:
29 "§ 51-2.1. Marriage of certain underage parties.
30 (a) A district court judge may issue an order authorizing a marriage between a person
31 over 16 years of age and under 18 years of age, to a person no more than four years older under
32 this section only upon finding as fact and concluding as a matter of law that the underage party
33 is capable of assuming the responsibilities of marriage and the marriage will serve the best
34 interest of the underage party. In determining whether the marriage will serve the best interest of
35 an underage party, the district court shall consider the following:
*S452-v-1*

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (1) The opinion of the parents of the underage party as to whether the marriage
2 serves the best interest of the underage party.
3 (2) The opinion of any person, agency, or institution having legal custody or
4 serving as a guardian of the underage party as to whether the marriage serves
5 the best interest of the underage party.
6 (3) The opinion of the guardian ad litem appointed to represent the best interest
7 of the underage party pursuant to G.S. 51-2.1(b) as to whether the marriage
8 serves the best interest of the underage party.
9 (4) The relationship between the underage party and the parents of the underage
10 party, as well as the relationship between the underage party and any person
11 having legal custody or serving as a guardian of the underage party.
12 (5) Any evidence that it would find useful in making its determination.
13 There shall be a rebuttable presumption that the marriage will not serve the best interest of
14 the underage party when all living parents of the underage party oppose the marriage. The fact
15 that the female is pregnant, or has given birth to a child, alone does not establish that the best
16 interest of the underage party will be served by the marriage.
17 (b) An underage party seeking an order granting judicial authorization to marry pursuant
18 to this section shall file a civil action in the district court requesting judicial authorization to
19 marry. The clerk shall collect court costs from the underage party in the amount set forth in
20 G.S. 7A-305 for civil actions in district court. Upon the filing of the complaint, summons shall
21 be issued in accordance with G.S. 1A-1, Rule 4, and the underage party shall be appointed a
22 guardian ad litem in accordance with the provisions of G.S. 1A-1, Rule 17. The guardian ad litem
23 appointed shall be an attorney and shall be governed by the provisions of subsection (d) of this
24 section. The underage party shall serve a copy of the summons and complaint, in accordance
25 with G.S. 1A-1, Rule 4, on the father of the underage party; the mother of the underage party;
26 and any person, agency, or institution having legal custody or serving as a guardian of the
27 underage party. The underage party also shall serve a copy of the complaint, either in accordance
28 with G.S. 1A-1, Rule 4, or G.S. 1A-1, Rule 5, on the guardian ad litem appointed pursuant to this
29 section. A party responding to the underage party's complaint shall serve his response within 30
30 days after service of the summons and complaint upon that person. The underage party may
31 participate in the proceedings before the court on his or her own behalf. At the hearing conducted
32 pursuant to this section, the court shall consider evidence, as provided in subsection (a) of this
33 section, and shall make written findings of fact and conclusions of law.
34 (c) Any party to a proceeding under this section may be represented by counsel, but no
35 party is entitled to appointed counsel, except as provided in this section.
36 (d) The guardian ad litem appointed pursuant to subsection (b) of this section shall
37 represent the best interest of the underage party in all proceedings under this section and also has
38 standing to institute an action under G.S. 51-2(c). The appointment shall terminate when the last
39 judicial ruling rendering the authorization granted or denied is entered. Payment of the guardian
40 ad litem shall be governed by G.S. 7A-451(f). The guardian ad litem shall make an investigation
41 to determine the facts, the needs of the underage party, the available resources within the family
42 and community to meet those needs, the impact of the marriage on the underage party, and the
43 ability of the underage party to assume the responsibilities of marriage; facilitate, when
44 appropriate, the settlement of disputed issues; offer evidence and examine witnesses at the
45 hearing; and protect and promote the best interest of the underage party. In fulfilling the guardian
46 ad litem's duties, the guardian ad litem shall assess and consider the emotional development,
47 maturity, intellect, and understanding of the underage party. The guardian ad litem has the
48 authority to obtain any information or reports, whether or not confidential, that the guardian ad
49 litem deems relevant to the case. No privilege other than attorney-client privilege may be invoked
50 to prevent the guardian ad litem and the court from obtaining such information. The
51 confidentiality of the information or reports shall be respected by the guardian ad litem, and no
Page 2 Senate Bill 452-First Edition

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 disclosure of any information or reports shall be made to anyone except by order of the court or
2 unless otherwise provided by law.
3 (e) If the last judicial ruling in this proceeding denies the underage party judicial
4 authorization to marry, the underage party shall not seek the authorization of any court again
5 under this section until after one year from the date of the entry of the last judicial ruling rendering
6 the authorization denied.
7 (f) Except as otherwise provided in this section, the rules of evidence in civil cases shall
8 apply to proceedings under this section. All hearings pursuant to this section shall be recorded
9 by stenographic notes or by electronic or mechanical means. Notwithstanding any other provision
10 of law, no appeal of right lies from an order or judgment entered pursuant to this section."
11 SECTION 3. G.S. 51-2.2 reads as rewritten:
12 "§ 51-2.2. Parent includes adoptive parent.
13 As used in this Article, the terms "parent", "father", or "mother" includes one who has become
14 a parent, father, or mother, respectively, by adoption."
15 SECTION 4. G.S. 51-3 reads as rewritten:
16 "§ 51-3. Want of capacity; void and voidable marriages.
17 All marriages between any two persons nearer of kin than first cousins, or between double
18 first cousins, or between a male person under 16 years of age and any female, or between a female
19 person under 16 years of age and any male, or between persons either of whom has a husband or
20 wife living at the time of such marriage, or between persons either of whom is at the time
21 physically impotent, or between persons either of whom is at the time incapable of contracting
22 from want of will or understanding, shall be void. No marriage followed by cohabitation and the
23 birth of issue shall be declared void after the death of either of the parties for any of the causes
24 stated in this section except for bigamy. A marriage contracted under a representation and belief
25 that the female partner to the marriage is pregnant, followed by the separation of the parties
26 within 45 days of the marriage which separation has been continuous for a period of one year,
27 shall be voidable unless a child shall have been born to the parties within 10 lunar months of the
28 date of separation."
29 SECTION 5. G.S. 51-16 reads as rewritten:
30 "§ 51-16. Form of license.
31 License shall be in the following or some equivalent form:
32 To any ordained minister of any religious denomination, minister authorized by a church, any
33 magistrate, or any other person authorized to solemnize a marriage under the laws of this State:
34 A.B. having applied to me for a license for the marriage of C.D. (the name of the man to be
35 written in full) of (here state his residence), aged ____ years (race, as the case may be), the son
36 of (here state the father and mother, if known; state whether they are living or dead, and their
37 residence, if known; if any of these facts are not known, so state), and E.F. (write the name of
38 the woman in full) of (here state her residence), aged ____ years (race, as the case may be), the
39 daughter of (here state names and residences of the parents, if known, as is required above with
40 respect to the man). (If either of the parties is under 18 years of age, the license shall here contain
41 the following:) And the written consent of G.H., father (or mother, etc., as the case may be) to
42 the proposed marriage having been filed with me, man) and there being no legal impediment to
43 such marriage known to me, you are hereby authorized, at any time within 60 days from the date
44 hereof, to celebrate the proposed marriage at any place within the State. You are required within
45 10 days after you shall have celebrated such marriage, to return this license to me at my office
46 with your signature subscribed to the certificate under this license, and with the blanks therein
47 filled according to the facts, under penalty of forfeiting two hundred dollars ($200.00) to the use
48 of any person who shall sue for the same.
49 Issued this ____ day of ____, ____
50 ____________________ L.M.
51 Register of Deeds of ____ County
