1 Every register of deeds shall, at the request of an applicant, designate in a marriage license
2 issued the race of the persons proposing to marry by inserting in the blank after the word "race"
3 the words "white," "black," "African-American," "American Indian," "Alaska Native," "Asian
4 Indian," "Chinese," "Filipino," "Japanese," "Korean," "Vietnamese," "Other Asian," "Native
5 Hawaiian," "Guamarian," "Chamorro," "Samoan," "Other Pacific Islander," "Mexican,"
6 "Mexican-American," "Chicano," "Puerto Rican," "Cuban," "Other Spanish/Hispanic/Latino," or
7 "other," as the case may be. The certificate shall be filled out and signed by the minister, officer,
8 or other authorized individual celebrating the marriage, and also be signed by two witnesses
9 present at the marriage, who shall add to their names their place of residence, as follows:
10 I, N.O., an ordained or authorized minister or other authorized individual of (here state to
11 what religious denomination, or magistrate, as the case may be), united in matrimony (here name
12 the parties), the parties licensed above, on the ___ day of ______, ___, at the house of P.R., in
13 (here name the town, if any, the township and county), according to law.
14 ________________ N.O.
15 Witness present at the marriage:
16 S.T., of (here give residence)."
17 SECTION 6. G.S. 51-17 reads as rewritten:
18 "§ 51-17. Penalty for issuing license unlawfully.
19 Every register of deeds who knowingly or without reasonable inquiry, personally or by
20 deputy, issues a license for the marriage of any two persons to which there is any lawful
21 impediment, or where either of the persons is under the age of 18 years, without the consent
22 required by law, shall forfeit and pay two hundred dollars ($200.00) to any parent, guardian, or
23 other person standing in loco parentis, who sues for the same: Provided, that requiring a party to
24 a proposed marriage to present a certified copy of his or her birth certificate, or a certified copy
25 of his or her birth record in the form of a birth registration card as provided in G.S. 130-102, in
26 accordance with the provisions of G.S. 51-8, shall be considered a reasonable inquiry into the
27 matter of the age of such party."
28 SECTION 7. This act becomes effective October 1, 2025, and applies to marriages
29 solemnized on or after that date.
